Preheat oven to 325 degrees F. Beat cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended. Add eggs, 1 at a time, mixing on low speed after each addition just until blended. Remove 1 cup of the batter; stir in pumpkin and spices. Pour remaining plain batter into crust. Top with pumpkin batter. Bake 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool. Refrigerate 3 hours or overnight.